    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review and strengthen enforcement of housing and equality laws in rental sector",
        "additional_details": "Homes found to breach environmental health laws should be confiscated and repurposed for social housing. We believe this would reduce the need to build on green belt land. We believe requiring the introduction of standardised systems for renting, rather than landlords and agents\u2019 discretion, would prevent breaches of the Equalities Act 2010.",
        "background": "The enforcement of laws relating to housing standards and equalities in the rental should be reviewed and strengthened, including introducing on the spot fines for landlords and agents breaking them. Accreditation and kite mark schemes should be required to remove agents found to break standards. ",
